<div class='commentinfo comment_'>
2005-06-20 11:18:05 (3267 days ago)
<div id='contact-8697'><span class='name'>michael martin</span><span class='send-message'><a href="/content/Contact/view/contactid/8697/display/detail/">Details</a></span></div> </div>
<div class='commentbox'>
We went down in Mid June, the water was cold, but not unbareable. Hiwassee Outfitters really took<br/>
care of us. The stretch we ran was a little over 6 miles. It had some nice, solid class II rapids<br/>
and several great surfing spots. Expect to paddle some flat water between the rapids. The Hiwassee<br/>
is pretty wide, we found the best rapids center or river left. We found a few holes, nothing that<br/>
wouldn't spit you out and if you like to play in holes, you will have fun with them. </div>
</td>
</tr>
